WEBVTT

00:01.668 --> 00:04.604
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.671 --> 00:12.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.479 --> 00:14.714
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.781 --> 00:16.449
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.516 --> 00:18.785
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.852 --> 00:24.457
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.524 --> 00:26.359
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.426 --> 00:30.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.731 --> 00:32.866
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:32.932 --> 00:33.867
[camera shutter clicks]

00:33.933 --> 00:35.135
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:35.201 --> 00:36.336
[camera shutter clicks]

00:36.403 --> 00:41.107
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:41.174 --> 00:42.308
[camera shutter clicks]

00:42.375 --> 00:43.109
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:43.176 --> 00:44.310
[camera shutter clicks]

00:44.377 --> 00:45.478
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:45.545 --> 00:46.479
[camera shutter clicks]

00:46.546 --> 00:48.014
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:48.081 --> 00:49.215
[camera shutter clicks]

00:49.282 --> 00:50.583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:50.650 --> 00:51.584
[camera shutter clicks]

00:51.651 --> 00:52.819
[loud smooching]

00:52.886 --> 00:53.820
[camera shutter clicks]

00:53.887 --> 00:56.423
- [giggling]

00:56.489 --> 00:57.424
[camera shutter clicks]

00:57.490 --> 01:02.862
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:02.929 --> 01:05.865
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

01:05.932 --> 01:14.073
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:16.576 --> 01:17.911
<i>- Cheers to good times</i>

01:17.977 --> 01:18.912
<i>with old buddies.</i>

01:18.978 --> 01:20.680
<i>- Old buddies, indeed.</i>

01:20.747 --> 01:23.116
<i>You know, I can't even remember</i>
<i>the last time</i>

01:23.183 --> 01:24.751
<i>we got to hang out one-on-one.</i>

01:24.818 --> 01:26.152
<i>- Seriously.</i>

01:26.219 --> 01:27.253
Moff, I'm sorry about not

01:27.320 --> 01:28.822
{\an1}being around as much
as I used to.

01:28.888 --> 01:31.024
Everything just gets
kind of crazy with a family,

01:31.090 --> 01:32.659
and now with another baby
on the way--

01:32.725 --> 01:34.027
ah, you know what I mean.

01:34.093 --> 01:36.262
- I wasn't listening
to a word you said.

01:36.329 --> 01:38.965
{\an3}I always zone out
when you talk about your family.

01:39.032 --> 01:42.569
{\an3}So how shall we begin
this glorious day?

01:42.635 --> 01:45.305
Perhaps watch
a ribald buddy comedy?

01:45.371 --> 01:47.740
Play an L-rated video game?

01:47.807 --> 01:49.075
Compose a rock opera?

01:49.142 --> 01:50.176
[guitar strums]

01:50.243 --> 01:51.945
- Well, heck, let's do it all.

01:52.011 --> 01:53.947
I got no responsibilities today.

01:54.013 --> 01:55.281
[knocking at door]

01:55.348 --> 01:57.784
- Oh, that must be the pizzas
I ordered.

01:57.851 --> 01:59.552
- Irving, I need your help.

01:59.619 --> 02:00.487
Baby.
- What?

02:00.553 --> 02:01.421
- Doctor.
- Doctor?

02:01.488 --> 02:02.655
- Ten minutes.
- Uh.

02:02.722 --> 02:04.224
{\an3}- I have to go to work
at the library.

02:04.290 --> 02:06.593
- Oh, oh, I completely forgot.

02:06.659 --> 02:07.627
[exclaiming]

02:07.694 --> 02:09.729
- But...hilarious buddy comedy?

02:09.795 --> 02:12.432
- Sorry, Moff, I--
I got to take a rain check.

02:12.499 --> 02:13.566
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:13.633 --> 02:14.567
- [sighs]

02:14.634 --> 02:15.802
Guess I should just go

02:15.869 --> 02:18.204
get into my sweatpants.

02:23.009 --> 02:24.944
<i>[phone ringing]</i>

02:25.011 --> 02:26.246
Yes, Irving.

02:26.312 --> 02:28.915
Harvey can stay at my place.

02:28.982 --> 02:30.049
[phone beeps]

02:30.116 --> 02:32.218
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:32.285 --> 02:33.853
{\an3}- You know what I love
about being a kid?

02:33.920 --> 02:34.954
{\an1}- [groans]

02:35.021 --> 02:36.122
- There's just so many things

02:36.189 --> 02:37.757
I don't understand yet.

02:37.824 --> 02:39.759
Like, what even is this thing?

02:39.826 --> 02:40.960
- No, no, no, no.

02:41.027 --> 02:42.362
Rule number one: no touching.

02:42.428 --> 02:43.997
{\an3}- Got it.

02:44.063 --> 02:46.432
I love rules.

02:46.499 --> 02:48.735
{\an1}- Hey, Harvey, we saw you
come over here to play.

02:48.801 --> 02:49.769
- Oh, hey, guys.

02:49.836 --> 02:51.604
{\an1}- [groaning]
Too many children.

02:51.671 --> 02:54.607
I agreed to babysit
one monster, not three.

02:54.674 --> 02:57.577
{\an1}- Hey, Moff, what's this stuff
called again?

02:57.644 --> 02:59.012
Smoke junk?

02:59.078 --> 03:00.747
Uh, smoke stacks?

03:00.813 --> 03:03.516
- It's called steampunk

03:03.583 --> 03:04.717
and, also, stop.

03:04.784 --> 03:06.853
- Well, can we play
video games, please?

03:06.920 --> 03:08.755
- [groaning]

03:08.821 --> 03:10.290
Quit touching my stuff!

03:10.356 --> 03:13.026
- Moff, you kind of seem upset.

03:13.092 --> 03:15.028
Did I do something wrong?

03:15.094 --> 03:16.663
- Oh, yes.

03:16.729 --> 03:19.999
You ruined my life.

03:20.066 --> 03:21.467
- What?

03:21.534 --> 03:24.170
- Your father and I used
to be first-class pals,

03:24.237 --> 03:26.272
a real dream team,

03:26.339 --> 03:28.441
and then he got busy

03:28.508 --> 03:31.077
and started making babies.

03:31.144 --> 03:34.881
{\an3}You ruined my friendship
with Irving.

03:34.948 --> 03:39.118
- I'm a--a--friendship-ruiner?

03:39.185 --> 03:40.486
- Oh, great.

03:40.553 --> 03:43.156
{\an3}I try so hard to suppress
unpleasant emotions,

03:43.222 --> 03:45.124
and now they're all
over the place.

03:45.191 --> 03:46.693
{\an1}All right.
[leaf blower hums]

03:46.759 --> 03:47.894
Everyone out.

03:47.961 --> 03:51.064
[leaf blower humming]

03:51.130 --> 03:53.066
- Harvey, you okay?

03:53.132 --> 03:55.001
<i>[somber music]</i>

03:55.068 --> 03:57.370
- What am I but a wedge

03:57.437 --> 03:59.405
driven between brothers?

03:59.472 --> 04:01.841
{\an3}- Oh, man, he only gets
sadly poetic

04:01.908 --> 04:04.510
when he's really bummed.

04:04.577 --> 04:07.113
- [sighs]

04:07.180 --> 04:08.247
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:08.314 --> 04:12.919
Is it--is it really my fault?

04:12.986 --> 04:14.220
Moff was right.

04:14.287 --> 04:17.490
I--I destroyed my Dad's life.

04:17.557 --> 04:19.225
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:19.291 --> 04:21.160
I'm a bad son.

04:21.226 --> 04:24.397
[groaning]

04:24.464 --> 04:25.198
[grunts]

04:25.264 --> 04:28.901
[groaning]

04:28.968 --> 04:30.269
[steam hissing]

04:30.336 --> 04:31.938
Is it true?

04:32.005 --> 04:34.140
Did I--did I do that?

04:34.207 --> 04:35.575
[groans]

04:35.642 --> 04:37.010
Steampunk...

04:37.076 --> 04:38.645
steampunk...

04:38.711 --> 04:40.179
steampunk...

04:40.246 --> 04:43.182
<i>[instrumental music]</i>

04:43.249 --> 04:44.350
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:44.417 --> 04:47.487
<i>[shimmering chimes]</i>

04:47.553 --> 04:52.025
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:52.091 --> 04:54.027
Gears.
Get your gears here.

04:54.093 --> 04:55.862
Gears of all shapes and sizes

04:55.928 --> 04:57.497
for all your steampunk needs.

04:57.563 --> 04:59.432
{\an1}- Oh, wow.
Those look great.

04:59.499 --> 05:02.935
{\an3}- Yes, sir, and I think I have
the perfect gear for you...

05:03.002 --> 05:03.970
{\an3}right here.

05:04.037 --> 05:06.506
Oh, hold on a second.

05:06.572 --> 05:09.042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:09.108 --> 05:10.043
Here you are.

05:10.109 --> 05:12.311
{\an1}- Oh, wow.

05:12.378 --> 05:13.846
It's perfect.

05:13.913 --> 05:14.847
Thank you.

05:14.914 --> 05:16.983
- No, thank <i> you.</i>

05:17.050 --> 05:18.251
{\an3}[sighs]

05:18.317 --> 05:23.156
♪ I'm just a little gear boy ♪

05:23.222 --> 05:25.992
♪ Selling my gears ♪

05:26.059 --> 05:28.194
♪ Year after year ♪

05:28.261 --> 05:30.630
♪ I'm not rich or big ♪

05:30.697 --> 05:33.332
♪ I'm poor and I'm small ♪

05:33.399 --> 05:37.236
♪ But who cares when I live
in the best city ♪

05:37.303 --> 05:39.605
♪ Of all ♪

05:39.672 --> 05:41.541
Steamberg!

05:41.607 --> 05:42.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:42.608 --> 05:45.511
♪ Every little cog and gear ♪

05:45.578 --> 05:47.146
♪ Yes, every little pipe
and valve ♪

05:47.213 --> 05:48.514
♪ I love them all so dear ♪

05:48.581 --> 05:51.651
♪ Every curly mustache
has a smile ♪

05:51.718 --> 05:53.986
♪ 'Cause in Steamberg, you
can't help but just be happy ♪

05:54.053 --> 05:55.188
♪ All the while ♪

05:55.254 --> 05:56.389
♪ There's gears and goggles ♪

05:56.456 --> 05:58.291
♪ And goggles and gears ♪

05:58.357 --> 06:00.093
♪ And goggles, goggles,
goggles, goggles ♪

06:00.159 --> 06:01.494
♪ Goggles, goggles, and gears ♪

06:01.561 --> 06:04.263
♪ Look, there's a robot
on the street ♪

06:04.330 --> 06:05.665
♪ He's made of copper ♪

06:05.732 --> 06:07.800
Wow, that's really,
really, really neat.

06:07.867 --> 06:11.170
♪ This wondrous place
where I belong ♪

06:11.237 --> 06:12.572
♪ As long as I can stay here ♪

06:12.638 --> 06:15.641
♪ Nothing ever will go wrong ♪

06:15.708 --> 06:17.477
♪ You might say
this genre's lame ♪

06:17.543 --> 06:19.278
♪ But the steam,
it calls my name ♪

06:19.345 --> 06:20.279
{\an1}- [whispering]
Harvey.

06:20.346 --> 06:21.814
- Oh, hello.

06:21.881 --> 06:24.550
♪ And today this
steampunk city's gonna fly ♪

06:24.617 --> 06:26.385
♪ La, la, la, la,
la, la, la, la, la ♪

06:26.452 --> 06:28.087
♪ La, la, la, la, la ♪

06:28.154 --> 06:29.422
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:29.489 --> 06:31.791
{\an3}- Are you excited
for the big day, sir?

06:31.858 --> 06:34.393
{\an1}- Why, yes, of course,
steam butler.

06:34.460 --> 06:36.863
♪ Mi, mi, mi, mi, mi, mi, mi ♪

06:36.929 --> 06:38.131
[clears throat]

06:38.197 --> 06:41.234
{\an3}- Would you like me to leave
while you sing, sir?

06:41.300 --> 06:43.069
{\an1}- Yes, this is
a personal ballad.

06:43.136 --> 06:44.337
You may go.

06:44.403 --> 06:46.773
{\an3}- Yes, sir.

06:46.839 --> 06:47.707
- [clears throat]

06:47.774 --> 06:50.143
♪ As mayor of Steamberg ♪

06:50.209 --> 06:52.445
♪ I've done quite a lot ♪

06:52.512 --> 06:54.847
♪ Built up this great city ♪

06:54.914 --> 06:57.183
♪ It's true ♪

06:57.250 --> 07:00.419
♪ And now thanks
to Irving the Inventor ♪

07:00.486 --> 07:02.155
♪ I've got ♪

07:02.221 --> 07:04.390
♪ The power to fly Steamberg ♪

07:04.457 --> 07:08.928
♪ To the big blue ♪

07:08.995 --> 07:10.730
- ♪ When you're living
here in Steamberg ♪

07:10.797 --> 07:12.532
all: ♪ It's like living
in a Dreamberg ♪

07:12.598 --> 07:13.900
- ♪ Every person
is impassioned ♪

07:13.966 --> 07:15.434
{\an3}- ♪ With impractical
old fashions ♪

07:15.501 --> 07:17.003
- Is it the future?
- Or the past?

07:17.069 --> 07:19.205
- Who even cares?
crowd: 'Cause it's a blast.

07:19.272 --> 07:21.574
all: ♪ Our spirits
will be high ♪

07:21.641 --> 07:25.745
♪ Once our mayor makes
this steampunk city ♪

07:25.812 --> 07:28.714
♪ Fly ♪

07:28.781 --> 07:32.151
[feet tapping]

07:32.218 --> 07:35.154
- [breathing heavily]

07:35.221 --> 07:36.956
[feet tapping]

07:37.023 --> 07:38.958
[sighing]

07:39.025 --> 07:41.661
[gasping]

07:41.727 --> 07:44.230
[coughing]

07:44.297 --> 07:46.365
[chuckles]

07:46.432 --> 07:49.035
[feet tapping]

07:49.101 --> 07:52.038
[chuckling]

07:52.104 --> 07:54.574
[feet tapping]

07:54.640 --> 07:56.275
Ha.

07:56.342 --> 07:58.845
- Is he--is he done?
Okay.

07:58.911 --> 08:00.680
[all cheering]

08:00.746 --> 08:03.382
- Ah, yes, thank you.
Thank you.

08:03.449 --> 08:05.852
I just started taking lessons.

08:05.918 --> 08:08.988
And now, the moment
we've all been waiting for.

08:09.055 --> 08:12.425
Today we turn on
the magical Power Crystal,

08:12.491 --> 08:15.661
granting our fair city
the ability to fly

08:15.728 --> 08:17.830
high above the clouds.

08:17.897 --> 08:20.566
[giggling]

08:20.633 --> 08:22.301
And none of this
would be possible

08:22.368 --> 08:24.837
without our master engineer,

08:24.904 --> 08:26.138
genius inventor,

08:26.205 --> 08:28.140
and my best friend,

08:28.207 --> 08:29.141
{\an1}Irving.

08:29.208 --> 08:32.311
[cheers and applause]

08:32.378 --> 08:34.347
{\an1}Are you ready to do this,
good chum?

08:34.413 --> 08:36.048
- You bet, buddy.

08:36.115 --> 08:39.919
crowd: Three, two, one.

08:39.986 --> 08:43.756
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

08:43.823 --> 08:45.091
[horns tooting]

08:45.157 --> 08:53.099
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:57.236 --> 08:59.038
- Wow.

08:59.105 --> 09:03.109
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:03.175 --> 09:04.110
- Yes!
- Whoo-hoo!

09:04.176 --> 09:05.278
We did it, buddy.

09:05.344 --> 09:06.545
{\an1}- Now, what do you say
we get a couple

09:06.612 --> 09:09.148
{\an1}of ice cream floats
to celebrate

09:09.215 --> 09:11.284
our float-ing city?

09:11.350 --> 09:12.285
[chuckling]

09:12.351 --> 09:14.120
{\an3}- [laughing]
This guy.

09:14.186 --> 09:15.221
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:15.288 --> 09:17.423
[gears grinding]

09:17.490 --> 09:18.557
- What's happening?

09:18.624 --> 09:20.459
[people shouting]

09:20.526 --> 09:22.662
- My gears!

09:22.728 --> 09:24.563
Hey, wait a second.

09:24.630 --> 09:26.132
Oh, there's a gear missing.

09:26.198 --> 09:27.566
[gears jamming]

09:27.633 --> 09:30.569
{\an3}- I must have made
some kind of miscalculation.

09:30.636 --> 09:32.271
- I can fix this.

09:32.338 --> 09:35.274
[people screaming]

09:35.341 --> 09:37.043
- Irving, what do we do?

09:37.109 --> 09:38.077
- I'm not sure.

09:38.144 --> 09:39.078
[metal clanking]

09:39.145 --> 09:40.079
What's that?

09:40.146 --> 09:42.882
[metal clanking]

09:42.949 --> 09:45.685
- [humming]

09:45.751 --> 09:46.752
Huh?

09:48.387 --> 09:49.322
[screaming]

09:49.388 --> 09:50.356
- Almost.

09:50.423 --> 09:51.357
Hmm.

09:51.424 --> 09:52.391
Nope.

09:52.458 --> 09:55.328
[both screaming and smooching]

09:55.394 --> 09:56.996
[both screaming]

09:57.063 --> 09:58.030
- [screaming]

09:58.097 --> 09:59.031
[metal clanking]

09:59.098 --> 10:01.000
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:01.067 --> 10:02.902
- That should do it.

10:02.969 --> 10:03.903
[metal clangs]

10:03.970 --> 10:11.811
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:11.877 --> 10:13.813
- [sighs]

10:13.879 --> 10:15.648
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:15.715 --> 10:17.616
{\an3}- Kid, where did you learn
to do that?

10:17.683 --> 10:19.585
- Oh, it was nothing, really.

10:19.652 --> 10:21.320
I just love gears.

10:21.387 --> 10:23.923
- I love gears.

10:23.990 --> 10:25.491
- I also love gears.

10:25.558 --> 10:27.126
- I just had an amazing idea.

10:27.193 --> 10:29.829
Little gear boy, would you
like to be my apprentice?

10:29.895 --> 10:31.397
{\an3}I'll teach you
everything I know.

10:31.464 --> 10:33.833
- That sounds...

10:33.899 --> 10:35.368
amaze-steam.

10:35.434 --> 10:38.070
{\an3}- [chuckles]
I love steam puns.

10:38.137 --> 10:39.705
- Uh, Irving,

10:39.772 --> 10:41.340
what about the ice cream floats?

10:41.407 --> 10:43.275
For the floating city.

10:43.342 --> 10:45.344
{\an3}- Do you mind if I take
a rain check on those, Moff?

10:45.411 --> 10:48.280
{\an3}I want to take my new apprentice
to see my valve collection.

10:48.347 --> 10:49.281
Would you like that?

10:49.348 --> 10:50.616
{\an1}- Would I!

10:50.683 --> 10:52.451
- I got all kinds of gears
and gadgets--

10:52.518 --> 10:53.552
{\an1}- Do you have copper?
And--and...

10:53.619 --> 10:54.954
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:55.021 --> 10:56.155
- [grumbling]

10:58.190 --> 11:00.192
<i>[instrumental music]</i>

11:00.259 --> 11:02.561
- Boy, it was really cool
how that little kid

11:02.628 --> 11:04.163
just fixed the city.

11:04.230 --> 11:06.399
- Yeah, kids can do anything...

11:06.465 --> 11:07.633
except vote.

11:07.700 --> 11:11.303
[gears grinding,
electricity sparking]

11:11.370 --> 11:13.606
[people screaming]

11:13.672 --> 11:16.709
{\an1}- Something is
not quite right here.

11:16.776 --> 11:18.811
{\an3}- [yells]
The whole city's tipping.

11:18.878 --> 11:22.014
Help, help, help,
help, help, help.

11:22.081 --> 11:23.282
- [yelling]

11:23.349 --> 11:24.850
- Disaster.

11:24.917 --> 11:27.286
The crystal which powers
our great city

11:27.353 --> 11:28.587
has been corrupted.

11:28.654 --> 11:30.523
[crystal shatters]

11:30.589 --> 11:32.024
- How could this happen?

11:32.091 --> 11:32.858
- That's terrible.

11:32.925 --> 11:34.393
- So we can't fly?

11:34.460 --> 11:38.397
- It was that piece of junk
stupid gear the boy used.

11:38.464 --> 11:40.099
It blew everything up.

11:40.166 --> 11:42.668
{\an1}It's going to take me weeks
to get a new crystal,

11:42.735 --> 11:45.571
all because of your dumb gear,

11:45.638 --> 11:47.640
crystal-breaker.

11:47.706 --> 11:48.841
- Crystal-breaker?

11:48.908 --> 11:51.377
I--I swear I--I fixed it.

11:51.444 --> 11:53.612
- Boo!
- You ruined this city.

11:53.679 --> 11:56.449
- There's only one
suitable punishment

11:56.515 --> 11:58.617
for crystal-breakers.

11:58.684 --> 12:01.520
[chortling]

12:01.587 --> 12:03.756
As mayor of Steamberg,

12:03.823 --> 12:06.992
I hereby find the boy guilty

12:07.059 --> 12:09.395
{\an3}for breaking the priceless
Power Crystal

12:09.462 --> 12:11.997
{\an3}and for thinking he's better
than everyone else

12:12.064 --> 12:15.434
{\an3}and for tearing apart
best friends,

12:15.501 --> 12:18.170
and for this, he must face

12:18.237 --> 12:24.043
the steam-shot!

12:24.110 --> 12:26.645
[metal clanking]

12:26.712 --> 12:29.148
Uh, someone get the glue gun.

12:29.215 --> 12:32.218
<i>[whimsical music]</i>

12:32.284 --> 12:33.719
Thank you, Louis.

12:33.786 --> 12:35.287
All right, off you go.

12:35.354 --> 12:39.391
{\an1}I sentence you to stay out
of my life forever.

12:39.458 --> 12:40.659
- Please don't do this.

12:40.726 --> 12:41.894
I can fix it.

12:41.961 --> 12:43.996
I--I don't want to leave.

12:44.063 --> 12:45.564
Uh, no, no, no.

12:45.631 --> 12:46.999
- And...
- Wait, please, please.

12:47.066 --> 12:48.067
- Good-bye.

12:48.134 --> 12:50.202
- I'm sorry it didn't work out.

12:50.269 --> 12:53.639
- [screaming]

12:53.706 --> 12:54.974
[crowd cheering]

12:55.040 --> 12:56.976
{\an3}- And now that
that's taken care of,

12:57.042 --> 13:00.579
how about that root beer float?

13:00.646 --> 13:03.582
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

13:03.649 --> 13:10.523
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:10.589 --> 13:12.691
{\an3}- [sighs]

13:12.758 --> 13:14.527
- Kick it here.
- [grunts]

13:14.593 --> 13:16.295
[air hisses]

13:16.362 --> 13:17.363
{\an3}- Aw, man.

13:17.429 --> 13:20.366
[distant screaming]

13:20.432 --> 13:22.401
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:22.468 --> 13:23.502
- [screaming]

13:23.569 --> 13:24.770
[grunts]

13:25.804 --> 13:28.841
{\an3}- Oh, my gosh,
a new ball.

13:28.908 --> 13:30.776
Aw, that's not a ball.

13:33.279 --> 13:35.915
- [breathing heavily]

13:35.981 --> 13:36.815
{\an3}- Hello?

13:36.882 --> 13:38.017
- Oh, hey, you're awake.

13:38.083 --> 13:39.952
{\an1}I thought you had
a nasty bump on your head.

13:40.019 --> 13:41.520
{\an1}Turns out it was just
your whole head.

13:41.587 --> 13:42.655
My name's Dade.

13:42.721 --> 13:44.290
- Oh, uh, nice to meet you.

13:44.356 --> 13:45.524
{\an3}I'm Harvey.

13:45.591 --> 13:47.593
- Harvey.
Wow, that's a cool name.

13:47.660 --> 13:48.727
You seem really cool.

13:48.794 --> 13:50.529
- Thank you, but I'm not.

13:50.596 --> 13:54.233
I'm just a worthless nobody who
ruins stuff for other people.

13:54.300 --> 13:56.502
- Oh, by golly, that's--
that's wonderful.

13:56.569 --> 13:58.871
That means you'll fit right in
around here.

13:58.938 --> 14:01.340
{\an3}- I don't--I don't even know
where I am.

14:01.407 --> 14:02.808
- Harvey, my sweet child,

14:02.875 --> 14:04.410
you're right where you belong,

14:04.476 --> 14:06.845
here with me in Reject Town.

14:06.912 --> 14:07.846
- Reject Town?

14:07.913 --> 14:09.281
- Best town in the world.

14:09.348 --> 14:11.584
{\an3}In fact, I'll tell you
about it right now

14:11.650 --> 14:13.219
{\an3}by singing.

14:13.285 --> 14:14.853
♪ Here in our town ♪

14:14.920 --> 14:16.455
♪ Called Reject Town ♪

14:16.522 --> 14:18.557
♪ So many wonders to be found ♪

14:18.624 --> 14:21.427
{\an3}♪ And I'd love to share
them all with you ♪

14:21.493 --> 14:22.595
- [coughing]

14:22.661 --> 14:24.430
- ♪ 'Cause in this magic world ♪

14:24.496 --> 14:25.698
♪ Of steampunk ♪

14:25.764 --> 14:28.033
♪ We built our town
out of steam junk ♪

14:28.100 --> 14:32.371
{\an1}♪ And I just know you're gonna
want to live here too ♪

14:32.438 --> 14:35.074
{\an1}♪ See, over there's
our playground ♪

14:35.140 --> 14:36.976
♪ And that's our public pool ♪

14:37.042 --> 14:38.510
Oh, and that's the library.

14:38.577 --> 14:40.512
You know, it doesn't really
have any books yet,

14:40.579 --> 14:43.015
but that's okay, 'cause none
of us know how to read anyway.

14:43.082 --> 14:45.017
- Wait, so you're saying
everything here

14:45.084 --> 14:46.986
is made out of garbage?
- Yep.

14:47.052 --> 14:49.054
♪ All the stuff
people throw out ♪

14:49.121 --> 14:51.724
♪ That no one wants
or cares about ♪

14:51.790 --> 14:53.859
♪ Living under trash can lids ♪

14:53.926 --> 14:58.030
♪ We're just a bunch
of worthless kids ♪

14:58.097 --> 14:59.798
- Oh, my gosh.
- Ah, you get used to it.

14:59.865 --> 15:01.233
Everyone does.

15:01.300 --> 15:03.502
{\an3}Say, let's go meet
some of the other rejects.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.938
{\an3}They can tell you all about
how great it is here.

15:06.005 --> 15:07.039
Oh, boy, oh, boy.

15:07.106 --> 15:08.607
This is gonna be fun.

15:08.674 --> 15:11.377
{\an3}- ♪ This is my life
in Reject Town ♪

15:11.443 --> 15:14.013
{\an3}♪ I sleep outside
and on the ground ♪

15:14.079 --> 15:17.549
{\an3}♪ On a bed of broken glass
and nails ♪

15:17.616 --> 15:20.886
♪ 'Cause things are tough
when you're rejected ♪

15:20.953 --> 15:23.188
♪ But it's the life
that I've accepted ♪

15:23.255 --> 15:24.857
♪ Why should I try for more? ♪

15:24.923 --> 15:27.426
♪ I'd only fail ♪

15:27.493 --> 15:30.029
- ♪ I'm always getting stung
by bees ♪

15:30.095 --> 15:32.398
- ♪ I burn my toys
so I don't freeze ♪

15:32.464 --> 15:37.236
all: ♪ And everyone's infected
with disease ♪

15:37.303 --> 15:39.738
{\an3}- ♪ Welcome
to my flower garden ♪

15:39.805 --> 15:41.774
♪ Watered with the tears I cry ♪

15:41.840 --> 15:43.742
♪ Whenever I feel hopeless ♪

15:43.809 --> 15:46.945
And I feel hopeless
almost all the time.

15:47.012 --> 15:49.548
- Uh, I think these flowers
are actually dead.

15:49.615 --> 15:50.983
- They are?
- Shh, shh.

15:51.050 --> 15:52.551
They're fine.
It's fine.

15:52.618 --> 15:54.787
Okay, thank you, Piri Piri.
- It was nice to meet you.

15:54.853 --> 15:56.088
{\an3}- See?
What'd I tell you, huh?

15:56.155 --> 15:57.656
{\an3}I just know you're gonna
like it here,

15:57.723 --> 15:58.924
{\an3}and everybody's gonna like
you.

15:58.991 --> 16:00.459
{\an3}I mean, 'cause I sure do
like you.

16:00.526 --> 16:01.427
Come on, everyone.

16:01.493 --> 16:02.494
Let's bring it home now

16:02.561 --> 16:03.962
for my new pal Harvey.

16:04.029 --> 16:06.932
all: ♪ Here in our town
called Reject Town ♪

16:06.999 --> 16:09.201
♪ The air we breathe
is grayish brown ♪

16:09.268 --> 16:13.072
♪ Our days are short,
our nights are sad and long ♪

16:13.138 --> 16:16.175
♪ Yeah, it's the life
we have to live ♪

16:16.241 --> 16:18.444
♪ 'Cause we've got
no alternative ♪

16:18.510 --> 16:22.981
♪ Our reject town
is where we all belong ♪

16:23.048 --> 16:28.554
♪ And now it's time for us
to end this song ♪

16:28.620 --> 16:30.456
[crashing]

16:30.522 --> 16:32.491
{\an3}- [gasping]

16:32.558 --> 16:33.659
So what do you say, buddy?

16:33.726 --> 16:34.793
You ready to move in?

16:34.860 --> 16:36.962
- Oh, goodness, no.
- What?

16:37.029 --> 16:38.864
{\an3}You--you hated our song,
didn't you?

16:38.931 --> 16:41.066
Oh, my gosh, I told you people

16:41.133 --> 16:43.268
{\an3}to watch your pitch,
ya bunch of hacks.

16:43.335 --> 16:45.738
- No, no, no, no, no.
The song was fine.

16:45.804 --> 16:49.141
It's just that--
guys, just because you're kids

16:49.208 --> 16:51.510
doesn't mean that you have
to live in garbage.

16:51.577 --> 16:52.945
You deserve better.

16:53.011 --> 16:54.680
- We do?
- Yeah.

16:54.747 --> 16:55.948
I know a wonderful place

16:56.014 --> 16:57.149
covered in gears,

16:57.216 --> 16:59.051
where you can eat
regular food

16:59.118 --> 17:01.086
and sleep in regular beds,

17:01.153 --> 17:02.654
and the streets are paved--

17:02.721 --> 17:03.655
- With gold?

17:03.722 --> 17:05.223
- No, but they're paved.

17:05.290 --> 17:07.092
It's called Steamberg.

17:07.159 --> 17:08.093
[all speaking at once]

17:08.160 --> 17:09.862
- It sounds amazing.

17:09.928 --> 17:12.364
- Oh, except I just remembered.

17:12.431 --> 17:13.766
I got kicked out.

17:13.832 --> 17:16.702
I messed up, and I broke
a really important crystal,

17:16.769 --> 17:18.971
but maybe if we find
another one,

17:19.037 --> 17:21.874
we could all go live
in Steamberg together.

17:21.940 --> 17:24.242
[all speaking at once]

17:24.309 --> 17:26.444
- But how are we supposed
to find a magic crystal?

17:26.512 --> 17:28.981
{\an3}- I don't think we have
crystals around here.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.582
All we have is tetanus.

17:30.649 --> 17:32.084
- Oh, well, looks like
you're just gonna have

17:32.151 --> 17:33.085
to stay here forever.

17:33.152 --> 17:34.153
You can live with me.

17:34.219 --> 17:35.788
- What about Randl's shop?

17:35.854 --> 17:38.857
{\an3}- Shut up!

17:38.924 --> 17:41.460
- Yeah, let's go to Randl's.

17:41.527 --> 17:43.328
<i>[wacky music]</i>

17:43.395 --> 17:46.031
- Crystals?
I don't think we have any--

17:46.098 --> 17:48.167
{\an1}- You boys want to see
a crystal?

17:48.233 --> 17:51.103
{\an1}My son here got me
a real nice crystal.

17:51.170 --> 17:52.571
Look at this right here.

17:52.638 --> 17:55.207
- Ma, how many times
do I have to tell you?

17:55.274 --> 17:56.708
That's just candy.

17:56.775 --> 18:00.078
I watched you steal it
out of a vending machine.

18:00.145 --> 18:03.382
{\an1}- Ooh, it's a juicy one,
children.

18:03.449 --> 18:04.450
- Unbelievable.

18:04.516 --> 18:06.218
- You're unbelievable.

18:06.285 --> 18:08.086
{\an3}- Okay.

18:08.153 --> 18:10.522
{\an3}So you don't have
any Power Crystals?

18:10.589 --> 18:12.424
- The only place
to get one of those

18:12.491 --> 18:15.894
is at the Crystal Cavern
of Madness, Majesty, and Chaos

18:15.961 --> 18:16.895
Supreme Mountain.

18:16.962 --> 18:18.197
{\an3}- Oh, cool.

18:18.263 --> 18:19.998
{\an3}Well, I guess we better
hit the road.

18:20.065 --> 18:21.166
- Not so fast.

18:21.233 --> 18:22.601
You got to have an airship

18:22.668 --> 18:25.237
before you can even dream
of reaching that place.

18:25.304 --> 18:27.105
{\an3}- Cool.
Do you got an airship?

18:27.172 --> 18:29.107
- No.
both: Aww.

18:29.174 --> 18:31.443
- But I'll tell you
where you can get one,

18:31.510 --> 18:32.778
for a price.

18:32.845 --> 18:35.614
- I don't have any money.

18:35.681 --> 18:38.984
- I like your hat.

18:39.051 --> 18:42.254
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:42.321 --> 18:44.289
- Harvey, be careful in here.

18:44.356 --> 18:47.392
Everyone is hopped up
on pop and pretzels.

18:47.459 --> 18:48.627
- Excuse me.

18:48.694 --> 18:49.728
Can anyone help me?

18:49.795 --> 18:52.598
I'm looking for the sky captain.

18:52.664 --> 18:54.833
[all gasp]

18:54.900 --> 18:57.369
- [whispering]
In the back.

18:57.436 --> 19:01.440
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:01.507 --> 19:02.708
- [crying]

19:02.774 --> 19:05.310
- I told you,
I wanted the crust cut off

19:05.377 --> 19:08.013
my grilled cheese sandwich.

19:08.080 --> 19:09.815
What are you
looking at, bighead?

19:09.882 --> 19:12.618
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:12.684 --> 19:16.054
- So I hear
you're a pretty good pilot.

19:16.121 --> 19:17.422
- I'm the best there is, kid.

19:17.489 --> 19:20.192
{\an1}I did the Steamell run
in 12 parsteams.

19:20.259 --> 19:22.561
- Oh, yeah?
Prove it.

19:22.628 --> 19:23.729
{\an1}- 'Kay.

19:23.795 --> 19:26.732
[imitating airplane sounds]

19:27.866 --> 19:29.535
- Ooh, she is really good.

19:29.601 --> 19:31.870
- Harvey, I don't like
the looks of these two.

19:31.937 --> 19:34.106
- [growling]

19:34.172 --> 19:35.607
- They seem cool,

19:35.674 --> 19:38.710
{\an1}and they're gonna fly us
to the cavern totally free.

19:38.777 --> 19:40.212
- Whoa, hold on there, buddy.

19:40.279 --> 19:41.813
Our services ain't free.

19:41.880 --> 19:42.948
They have a fee.

19:43.015 --> 19:45.117
- Yeah, a fee.
What Fee said.

19:45.183 --> 19:47.152
- But I don't have anything.

19:47.219 --> 19:49.087
{\an3}- Okay, then I guess
we'll just be on our way.

19:49.154 --> 19:50.455
Sorry to have wasted your time.

19:50.522 --> 19:51.857
See you never again.

19:51.924 --> 19:54.526
- Wait, I do have something:

19:54.593 --> 19:57.930
the most precious thing
in the whole universe.

19:57.996 --> 20:00.065
- Empanadas?

20:00.132 --> 20:03.468
- Oh, those are pretty good,
but, no.

20:03.535 --> 20:08.206
I'm talkin' 'bout friendship.

20:08.273 --> 20:09.641
- What's a friendship?

20:09.708 --> 20:11.944
- Friendship is something
that supports you,

20:12.010 --> 20:13.445
can carry you forever,

20:13.512 --> 20:15.414
and never ever gives up on you,

20:15.480 --> 20:17.482
runs around,
or deserts you.

20:17.549 --> 20:20.185
- That sounds like
an impressive ship,

20:20.252 --> 20:22.087
and you say we can
have it forever?

20:22.154 --> 20:24.756
- It's all yours,
if you want it.

20:24.823 --> 20:26.692
- Can it carry a lot of people?

20:26.758 --> 20:28.160
Or even empanadas?

20:28.226 --> 20:30.062
- Friendship can do anything.

20:30.128 --> 20:33.065
both: Whoa.

20:33.131 --> 20:34.700
- You've got yourself a deal.

20:34.766 --> 20:37.002
- Yeah!
- Ugh, nuts.

20:37.069 --> 20:38.003
[glasses clink]

20:38.070 --> 20:40.906
both: To friendship.

20:40.973 --> 20:42.140
- Whoa.

20:42.207 --> 20:43.675
This thing is great.

20:43.742 --> 20:46.812
Stuff with faces is, like,
the best stuff.

20:46.878 --> 20:47.913
- All right.

20:47.980 --> 20:49.147
{\an1}We got a lot of flying
ahead of us,

20:49.214 --> 20:50.882
so let's move on out.

20:50.949 --> 20:53.885
- I hope you have barf bags,
'cause sometimes I get seasick

20:53.952 --> 20:57.089
and airsick and ground-sick.

20:57.155 --> 20:59.524
- [murmured chittering]

20:59.591 --> 21:02.194
{\an1}- I better let the boss know
about this.

21:02.260 --> 21:05.063
{\an1}- So, Irving, how about
we catch a matinee?

21:05.130 --> 21:07.132
Or a matin-B or a matin-C?

21:07.199 --> 21:08.700
Any of the matins.
They're all great.

21:08.767 --> 21:10.802
{\an3}- Sounds good, buddy,
but I'm still trying to fix

21:10.869 --> 21:12.004
this doohickey.

21:12.070 --> 21:14.373
[phone ringing]
- Oh, excuse me.

21:14.439 --> 21:15.707
{\an1}Hello?

21:15.774 --> 21:17.509
They did what?

21:17.576 --> 21:21.480
{\an1}[stammering]
Excuse me, Irving.

21:21.546 --> 21:24.716
{\an1}I got to go to the, uh,
butt doctor

21:24.783 --> 21:26.018
for my, you know.

21:26.084 --> 21:28.153
For my butt.

21:28.220 --> 21:29.154
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:29.221 --> 21:32.290
[groaning]

21:32.357 --> 21:35.193
Oh, that boy thinks he can
come back here

21:35.260 --> 21:36.895
and take my friend?

21:36.962 --> 21:37.896
[grunts]

21:37.963 --> 21:40.899
<i>[bombastic music]</i>

21:40.966 --> 21:43.935
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:44.002 --> 21:45.937
Fly, my Fredd Bots.

21:46.004 --> 21:47.773
Fly!

21:47.839 --> 21:49.007
Oh, I'm slipping.

21:49.074 --> 21:51.076
Guys, I have
a really good feeling

21:51.143 --> 21:53.111
that nothing
is gonna stop us.

21:53.178 --> 21:55.647
- I'm going to stop him!

21:55.714 --> 21:58.583
{\an3}[cackling]

22:01.520 --> 22:04.656
<i>[exciting music]</i>

22:04.723 --> 22:12.664
<i>♪ ♪</i>
